    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A medium to strong violet pigment composed of cobaltous phosphate; it was first developed in 1859 by Salvetat and sold as an artists' pigment in 1890. The colorfast pigment has low tinting strength and dries quickly in oil paints.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
